-- Brazil Sets Auction for Power Contracts Including Wind and Solar
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-07-08T13:30:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-08/brazil-sets-auction-for-power-contracts-including-wind-and-solar.html
Power-plant developers in  Brazil  will
bid for contracts to sell energy on Oct. 25 from projects due to
go into operation in three years.  Developers of wind farms, solar projects, natural gas-fired
power plants and biomass facilities will bid for 20-year
contracts in the so-called A-3 auction, according to a notice
today in Brazilâ€™s official  gazette . Companies proposing
hydroelectric dams will bid for 30-year contracts.  The power plants must produce electricity by Jan. 1, 2016,
according to the online notice. Participants have until Aug. 13
to register for the government-organized event.  To contact the reporter on this story:
